content.description: Move up the white pillar with high feet, then make a big reach out to the white block across the gravel.  Make a lot of stemy moves to top out.
content.location: Physical Education East Building, near the entrance.

content.description:
Horizontal thin hand crack to vertical finger crack in concrete joints next to stairwell.  Face holds make this easier. 

  Route entered for historical purposes only.
content.protection: You could maybe put gear in the cracks, but this is most often bouldered.  Traverse a couple moves to the stairs to get down.
content.location: Located on the stairwell on the SW corner of the Tyler Street Parking Structure at the NW corner of Tyler St & McAllister Ave.

content.description: Start left hand on the hinge, right hand on the door handle, heel hook out left and climb the hinges to the top of the power supply.
content.location: West of the Engineering Center A Building, across Palm Walk.

content.description: Start on second row of deep pockets, make big moves up the pockets, tap the Interdisciplinary Science sign to finish.
Move up the white door using the edges and the hinges to the final mail slot pocket at the top.  Then reach out right to the brick pillar and top out.
content.location: Physical Education East Building, near the main entrance.

content.description:
Lieback, stem, & jam up corner. 

  Route entered for historical purposes only.
content.protection: None.  Don't fall.  Downclimb to get off.
content.location: On east side of Bateman Physical Sciences Center, SE of & around the corner from Math Chimney.

content.description:
A (sparsely) bolted roped climbing route right on campus.  Sustained 5.8 chimney passes one bolt at 25', an old hangerless bolt at 50', then nothing to the top.  There used to be another bolt at about 75' but this has supposedly been removed & the hole filled.  Since this route is somewhat secluded and ideal for night-time ascents, it has historically been climbed at night, and often after an evening on Mill Ave.  Also this route is very R/X rated and should be taken seriously.   

  Of course I would never do this.  Route entered for historical purposes only.
content.protection: All you get is 1 bolt & 1 hangerless bolt in 100'.  Rap off piping on the roof.
content.location: Tucked back in a corner on east side of Bateman Physical Sciences Center.

content.description: Start inside the archway on the door hinges, and move out left onto either Florito Family Stairway route.
content.protection: Big Crash pad to protect the stairs

content.description: Start at the right of the archway, make moves up the   rock-like walls and top out where the banister becomes flat.
Start to the left of the archway and move up to where the stairway banister becomes flat.  Top out.
Start on the door handle and move up the door hinges and brick edging.  move up to metal edging and top out at the top of the staircase.
content.location: Engineering Center Building A wing, northeast side.

content.description: Climb up the brick pillar with tiny incuts, move straight up to the turquoise girder, and top out at the balcony.
Move up the white pillar and brick wall, make a big reach to the secret ledge underneath the roof, move out the protruding white feature and top out.  Top out is a little sketchy.
content.location: Business Administration Building, east side.  Start on the pillar to the right of the main sign.

content.description:
A serious route!  Climb protruding bricks to top.  Downclimb or find something to rap off of.  Discretion is advised. 

  Route listed for historical purposes only.
content.location: Located in the notch on the north side of the west face of the Biodesign Institue "A", about 40' south of the north face.  Biodesign Institute "A" is llocated on the NE corner of McAllister Ave & Terrace Rd.

content.description:
Armstrong Hall has several buttresses on it's north & south sides, climb any one.  Whichever you choose, the crux is up high where the angle increases to vertical.  This route is x-rated and should be taken seriously. 

  The north side has grassy landings, but the south side is more hidden.  Pick your poison. 

  Route entered for historical purposes only.
content.protection: No pro.  All buttresses are R/X.  Try not to fall.
content.location: Southwest corner of Orange Mall & Macallister Ave.

content.description:
Lots of fun stuff on campus.  There is even a bolt protected roped route here!  Discretion is advised. 

  Routes are listed for historical purposes only.
